    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e60c45a0_784fe298",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/sink_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 16
      },
      "lineNbr": 41,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-29T01:01:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My previous commit was actually made with the exact same code.:)\nHowever, all sub-conveys shared the same server instance listening on the same port, and interfere each other. For example, even if a sub convey closes the server, the server is still available by another process forked with the same HTTP server.\n\nThus, it was necessary to repeat `installTestListener(srv)` and `defer cleanup()` in each sub test, and I added startWithTestListener() to reduce a couple of lines in every test.",
      "parentUuid": "41366416_45f7c16e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 41,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "f19cc3bf4bef45d090ce70b30f47d5c7b0ddafa6",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "68caf73d_a613df81",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/sink_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 16
      },
      "lineNbr": 41,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-29T08:11:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "sub-conveys do not share memory, e.g.\n\n Convey {\n    obj \u003d NewObject()\n    Convey {\n    }\n    Convey{\n    }\n }\n\neven if the leads execute concurrently, obj\u003dNewObject() is executed for each of them independently.\nSo I think each of conveys should get different port.\n\nwhich commit are you referring to? maybe there was another bug",
      "parentUuid": "e60c45a0_784fe298",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 41,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 41,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "f19cc3bf4bef45d090ce70b30f47d5c7b0ddafa6",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
